Portions of explore.py derive from that source, at varying degrees of fidelity:

  - S4Model                          — TAKEN NEAR-VERBATIM from s4/example.py
                                       (S4Model). Lightly modified only: comments
                                       stripped, lines condensed, dropout_fn
                                       hardcoded to nn.Dropout1d, lr and default
                                       hyperparameters changed. Forward logic is
                                       line-for-line the original.
  - SSMLayer conv branch             — the FFT convolution (rfft/irfft) is taken
                                       near-verbatim from s4/models/s4/s4d.py
                                       (S4D.forward); the kernel is rebuilt from
                                       explicit dA/dB/dC (adapted).
  - discretize()                     — ADAPTED: the ZOH expressions are from
                                       s4/models/s4/s4d.py (S4DKernel.forward),
                                       restructured to return dA, dB, dC as
                                       separate tensors instead of folding them
                                       into the convolution kernel.
  - SSMLayer recurrent branch        — ADAPTED: the diagonal step recurrence
                                       (state = dA*state + dB*u; y = 2*Re(dC*state))
                                       derives from s4/models/s4/s4.py
                                       (SSMKernelDiag.step); the surrounding
                                       quantization / clamp / error-feedback /
                                       diagnostics code is original.

Significant change from the original: the discrete state-space matrices
(dA, dB, dC) are kept as explicit tensors and quantized per-forward, rather than
being folded directly into the convolution kernel, to enable quantization of the
recurrent state and the state matrix.
